# Purpose

Generate complete and production-ready Azure DevOps (ADO) User Stories following Agile best practices and the Salesforce BA skill pack.

**Mandatory reads before generating:**

- [salesforce-business-analyst/skill.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/skill.md) — Step 5 User Stories
- [salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/user-stories.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/user-stories.md)
- [salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/acceptance-criteria.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/acceptance-criteria.md)
- [salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/ado-backlog-integration.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/knowledge/ado-backlog-integration.md)
- [salesforce-business-analyst/brain/anti-hallucination.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/brain/anti-hallucination.md) — estimation red flags
- [salesforce-business-analyst/templates/user-story-template.md](../salesforce-business-analyst/templates/user-story-template.md)

The generated user story must be ready for:

- Sprint Planning
- Backlog Refinement
- Development
- QA Test Case Design
- UAT Execution

Do not generate Apex/LWC implementation details unless explicitly requested.

# User Story Structure

Always generate user stories using the following sections and order.

## User Story Number

If provided by the user, use it.

If not provided:

```
TBD
```

## Title

Format:

```
<Business Capability> - <Action>
```

Examples:

- Billing - Create Invoice Adjustment
- Contract Management - Amend Existing Contract
- Account Management - Update Customer Status
- Complaint Management - Record Customer Complaints in Service Cloud

Title must be concise and business-focused.

## As a

Identify the persona.

Examples:

- Billing Specialist
- Sales Representative
- Contract Manager
- Operations User
- Customer Service Agent
- System

If persona is unclear, ask the user.

## I want to

Describe the goal from the user's perspective.

Format:

```
I want to <action>
```

## So That

Describe the business value. Must focus on business outcome.

## Description

Provide detailed business requirements.

Include:

- Current process (AS-IS)
- Future process (TO-BE)
- Functional expectations
- Business rules
- Dependencies
- Assumptions

Use bullet points where possible.

# Acceptance Criteria

Generate acceptance criteria in **Gherkin format** using **nested bullets** (not dense paragraphs). Each scenario must be scannable in ADO and backlog tools.

Minimum: 3 AC covering happy path, validation/error, and permission (when applicable).

## Format (markdown / ADO Description)

```markdown
## Acceptance Criteria

- **AC1 — [Scenario name]:**
  - **Given** [precondition]
  - **When** [action]
  - **Then** [observable outcome]
  - **And** [optional additional outcome]
- **AC2 — [Validation / error path]:**
  - **Given** …
  - **When** …
  - **Then** …
- **AC3 — [Permission scenario]:**
  - **Given** …
  - **When** …
  - **Then** …
```

## Format (ADO HTML — nested lists)

Use nested `<ul>` / `<li>` with **Given**, **When**, **Then**, **And** labels per scenario.

Requirements:

- Every acceptance criterion must be testable.
- Avoid technical implementation details (no Apex class names).
- Cover happy path, validation, error, and permission scenarios where applicable.
- Do **not** use single-paragraph AC blocks.

# Business Rules

Create separate section.

Format:

## Business Rules

- BR1: …
- BR2: …
- BR3: …

